        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: Rust/GTK4 Linux companion app (#75, alternative track)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a native Linux desktop companion under `apps/linux-gtk/` written in **Rust + GTK4 + libadwaita**\n- Alternative-track contribution for [#75](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/75) alongside @tiagonix's C/GTK4 work at `apps/linux/` — different language, zero path conflicts, same gateway protocol\n- Steady base, early. Needs security review, packaging, and UI polish\n\n## Why another one\n\nI started on a prototype using web-tech (Electron) before reading through #75, then saw [@steipete's comment](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/75#issuecomment-3747113141):\n\n> My vision for this is a cute gtk-native Linux app. Esp for the statusbar features.\n\nSwitched tracks to native GTK. @tiagonix's C implementation was the reference, but I wanted to see what the Rust ecosystem gives us here (borrow-checked gateway client, fewer NULL pointer surprises, tokio for async RPC, `cargo test` for unit coverage).\n\nHappy to fold it in, leave it as a community showcase, or archive it — whichever serves the project.\n\n## What's included\n\n**Library crate** (`crates/gateway-client/`, no GTK dependency):\n- Async tokio + tungstenite WebSocket client with auto-reconnect\n- Typed request/event frames (serde_json-backed)\n- Device identity with ed25519 challenge signing\n- Env > config-file > defaults resolution for URL / token / TLS\n- 24 unit tests\n\n**GTK4 app** (`crates/app/`):\n- AdwOverlaySplitView main window with responsive sidebar (collapses < 600sp)\n- Bridge layer pumping tokio events into GLib main loop via async-channel\n- 17 views: Chat, Overview, Agents, Channels, Sessions, Skills, Usage, Cron, Retros, Workflows, Instances, Logs, Config, Settings, Debug, Control Room, About\n- **Chat**: live send/receive with Markdown rendering, per-session model picker (`sessions.patch`), typing indicator, thinking/tool-call toggles, history via `chat.history`\n- **Agents**: master/detail with editable settings (`agents.update`) and workspace files (`agents.files.list`)\n- Snapshot refresh pattern: parallel `agents.list` / `sessions.list` / `models.list` / `channels.status` RPCs on connect\n- 42 unit tests\n\n**Supporting files**: .desktop, .metainfo.xml, SVG icon, CSS (orange accent + libadwaita theming), README with per-distro build instructions\n\n## Known gaps\n\n- **Security review needed** — device identity handling, TLS verification flow, token persistence\n- No packaging yet (Flatpak/deb/AppImage) — build-from-source only\n- Tool-call rendering is basic (JSON in collapsible blocks)\n- No system tray on tiling WMs (StatusNotifierWatcher absent) — fails gracefully\n- Config editor is read-only\n- Polling timers could be replaced with event-driven updates\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `cargo build --release` — zero warnings\n- [x] `cargo test --release` — 66 tests pass (24 gateway-client + 42 app)\n- [x] Smoke-tested against gateway v2026.4.3 on Arch Linux (bspwm/X11, Cairo renderer)\n- [ ] Test on Wayland / GNOME Shell\n- [ ] Test on Ubuntu 24.04 with stock GTK4/libadwaita packages\n- [ ] Security audit of device identity + TLS flow\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
